g.text: When a requestor asks for an audit,
the contract QuantstampAudit adds a request
and emits an event that Audit nodes listen to.
Only one node will get assigned the audit when they call
getNextAuditRequest(). The function will set the auditor in the contract
and will lock the auditor node's funds.
The audit node submits a report and the report's information gets stored in
The report gets assigned to police nodes which are notified by events. The police nodes check the report and submit their assessments.
Finally, the report is ready and the requestor can read its content.
